726580f-a.title: Queens: Flushing Avenue - Woodward Avenue
726580f-a.text:
1355 Flushin Ave., west side, between Woodward and Metropolitan
Aves., showing the G. Thomas Smith farmhouse, later owned by his son. It
is now owned by Andrew Bauer Jr. A new front has been put on this house.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726586f-a.title: Queens: Flushing Avenue - Woodward Avenue
726586f-a.text:
Flushing Ave. (center of view), between Woodward Avenue (left) and
Metropolitan Ave. (right). In the background is the 4-story structure
of the Ideal Chair Company, which faces on Metropolitan Ave. To the
rimht of it, on the north side of Metropolitan Ave., between 49th and
50th Streets, is an old house (cupola thereonl. In front of the factory
building is a peaked roof house, known as the Gabriel house which was
erected by Todd the publisher. Be sold to one McGovern, who sold it to
H.C. Bohack Company; the latter demolishing same.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726591f-a.title: Queens: Flushing Avenue - Woodward Avenue
726591f-a.text:
Flushing Ave., west side, between Woodward and Metropolitan Aves.,
showing the Cochrane house (No. 1359 Flushing Ave; tree in front of)
in a set of four views. View No. 3 shows the Cochrane home alone,
the house to the right of it having been demolished in the interim.
The Jacob sash-factory (4-story), seen at the right, faces on Metro-
politan Ave. In 1929 it was the Ideal Chair Company.
1922.
Views 1 \& 2.
View 31 September 1928.
View 4: April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726592f-b.title: Queens: Flushing Avenue - Woodward Avenue
726592f-b.text:
Flushing Ave., at the S.W. corner of Woodward Ave., showing in a
set of four views the Woodward house. This house, supposedly erected by
Joseph Woodward in 1750, stands 6O feet south of Woodward Ave. and in
rear of 1471 Flushing Ave.,on land formerly owned by the Schenck family.
In 1852 it belonged to the Schoomaker Estate; from 1869-1873 to N. Hausmann.
For ore cata aee the N.. Sun. '~P(SS9f S. 1239.
Views 2 \& 3: September 1928.
View 4: April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

728236f-b.title: Queens: Woodward Avenue - Flushing Avenue
728236f-b.text:
Woodward Ave., east from Flushing Ave., showing at the N.W. corner
(rear view 3 story frame) No. 1473 Flushing Ave. On the other corner is
the Diehl house, operated as a saloon by one Schleider. The three story
building was in a delapidated condition in 1934. This is a set of four
views.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
